com.ibm.team.repository.client.util

Class ClientLibraryFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ibm.team.repository.client.util.ClientLibraryFactory

  • public abstract class ClientLibraryFactory
extends java.lang.Object
    The base class of all client library factory implementations. Components must register their implementation of the ClientLibraryFactory class using the com.ibm.team.repository.client.clientLibraryFactory extension point.

    The createClientLibrary method of the client library factory will be called to get an instance that implements the component's primary client library interface. It's called only once and the same client library instance is available for the lifetime of a ITeamRepository instance.

    Since:
    0.5

    • Method Detail

      • createClientLibrary

        public abstract java.lang.Object createClientLibrary(IClientLibraryContext context)
        Creates an instance of the client library. There is one client library instance created for each ITeamRepository instance. The context provides specialized access to the team repository services. The context must not meant to be passed around to clients of the client library.
        Parameters:
        context - the client library context object with which the new client library instance is to be associated.
        Returns:
        the client library instance; which is never null
